problem_prompt: Solve the following problem. Find the integer $n$, $0 \le n \le 11$, such that \[n \equiv 10389 \pmod{12}.\]
solution: Since $10389 \equiv 9 \pmod{12}$, the integer $n$ we seek is $n = \boxed{9}$.
gpt_response: We have that $10389 \equiv 9 \pmod{12}$. Since $0 \le n \le 11$ and $9$ is the remainder when $10389$ is divided by $12$, we have $n = \boxed{9}$.
